  <title id="GUID-A4D3FF66-A7CF-4FFC-B107-CCF41F85472A">About the Policy Screen</title>
  <refbody>
    <section id="GUID-3A481E02-9073-4F55-B437-517CA325F21D">
      <p id="steps_policy_screen"><indexterm>policy</indexterm>Click the
          <uicontrol>Agents</uicontrol> tab in the top navigation bar of the StellarOne web console.
        Click the <uicontrol>All</uicontrol> group, and then a screen displays the second level of
        groups/agents managed by StellarOne. Navigate to the target agent or group, and then click
        its corresponding <uicontrol>Policy Inheritance</uicontrol>
          (<uicontrol>Inherited</uicontrol>, <uicontrol>Customized</uicontrol>, or
          <uicontrol>Self-managed</uicontrol>). Then the <wintitle>Policy</wintitle> screen
          appears.<note id="note_h5h_bww_m5b">
          <p>You can also click the the corresponding <uicontrol>Policy Inheritance</uicontrol> link
            of the <uicontrol>All</uicontrol> group to check it's policy settings.</p>
        </note></p>
      <fig id="fig_asp_jmv_35b" otherprops="PRINT" outputclass="PRINT">
        <title>Switch Options of the Policy Screen</title>
        <image href="../images/policyScreenOptions=20220815140042.png" id="image_lyn_bxw_m5b"/>
      </fig>
      <table frame="all" id="table_ohx_dxw_m5b">
        <title>Switch Options of the Policy Screen</title>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
          <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>
                <p>Options</p>
              </entry>
              <entry>
                <p>Description</p>
              </entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry>
                <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Product (function
                    type)</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Funtion Type</uicontrol></p>
              </entry>
              <entry>
                <p>The dropdown button next to the <uicontrol>Function Type</uicontrol> allows users
                  to switch between <uicontrol>StellarProtect</uicontrol> and
                    <uicontrol>StellarProtect (Legacy Mode)</uicontrol>.</p>
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>
                <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Policy Inheritance</indexterm><uicontrol>Policy
                      Inheritance</uicontrol></indexterm></p>
              </entry>
              <entry>
                <p>The toggle button allows users to enable or disable the group policy inheritance
                  from the parent group.</p>
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>
                <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Self-management</indexterm><uicontrol>Self-management</uicontrol></indexterm></p>
              </entry>
              <entry>
                <p>The toggle button allows users to enable or disable the agent's self-management,
                  which will set the agent free from StellarOne console's policy management.</p>
              </entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry>
                <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>General
                    Info/Policy</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>General
                    Info</uicontrol>/<uicontrol>Policy</uicontrol></p>
              </entry>
              <entry>
                <p>The tabs allow users to switch between the displays of General Information or
                  Policy settings.</p>
              </entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
    </section>
    <section>
      <fig id="fig_qnv_zyw_m5b" otherprops="PRINT">
        <title>Functions of the Policy Screen</title>
        <image href="../images/policyScreenFunctions=20220815140407.png" id="image_rnv_zyw_m5b"/>
      </fig>
    </section>
    <table frame="all" rowsep="1" colsep="1" id="table_tt1_nmv_35b">
      <title>Functions of the Policy Screen</title>
      <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
        <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="1*"/>
        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p>Function</p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>Description</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Application
                  Lockdown</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Application Lockdown</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function provides protection by only allowing the access of the applications
                that are in the Approved List. Please refer to <xref
                  href="applicationLockdown=20220729151400.xml"/> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Industrial-Grade Next-Generation
                  Antivirus</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Industrial-Grade Next-Generation
                  Antivirus</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>The industrial-grade next-generation antivirus provides real-time and scheduled
                scan settings. Please refer to <xref
                  href="industrialGradeNextGenAv=20220813050723.xml"/> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Agent Component Update
                  Schedule</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Agent Component Update
                  Schedule</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>Users can schedule the component update for agents. Please refer to <xref
                  href="scanComponentUpdateSchedule=20220727154928.xml"/> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Operation Behavior Anomaly
                  Detection</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Operation Behavior Anomaly
                  Detection</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function provides protection against fileless attacks. Please refer to <xref
                  href="obad=20220803162325.xml"/> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>OT Application
                  Safeguard</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>OT Application
                Safeguard</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function ensures continuous operations by allowing the ICS applications
                recognized by StellarProtect to be updated without being blocked or restricted.
                Please refer to <xref href="otApplicationSafeguard=20220813043211.xml"/> for more
                details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>DLL Injection
                  Protection</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>DLL Injection
                Protection</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function provides protection against DLL hijacking attacks. Please refer to
                  <xref href="dllInjectionProtection=20220813043642.xml"/> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Device Control</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Device
                  Control</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function provides protection against unauthorized access of USB devices.
                Please refer to <xref href="deviceControl=20220813051321.xml"/> for more
                details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>User-Defined Suspicious
                  Objects</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>User-Defined Suspicious
                  Objects</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function allows users to manually add suspicious file hashes or paths to
                prevent the endpoints from be infected by these files. Please refer to <xref
                  href="userDefinedSuspicious=20220813044821.xml"/> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Agent Password</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Agent
                  Password</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function allows the administrators to change the StellarProtect admin password
                for all connected endpoints via StellarOne console. Please refer to <xref
                  href="agentPassword=20220813045107.xml"/> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Patch</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Patch</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function allows the administrator to deploy patch files to all agents under
                the same group policy. Please refer to <xref href="patchTask=20220815002505.xml"/>
                for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry>
              <p><indexterm>policy<indexterm>Trusted
                  Certificates</indexterm></indexterm><uicontrol>Trusted
                Certificates</uicontrol></p>
            </entry>
            <entry>
              <p>This function allows the administrator to add new trusted certificates in the
                policy settings. Please refer to <xref href="trustedCertificates=20220813045623.xml"
                /> for more details.</p>
            </entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
  </refbody>
